name: Kathleen Regan - see ya next year (ft. brother bird)

attributes.trait_type: see ya next year (ft. brother bird)

metadata.description:
see ya next year (ft. brother bird)

we wanted to write a song for the slow days after the holidays, and before the end of the year.. when you're reflective about the long year that went by too fast, while simultaneously being excited for the new one.

To my current collectors, thanks so much for being such a big part of my 2022, I'm wildly grateful for the support and community I found this year.  I have high hopes for the music nft fam in 2023 :) xo


**
I AM THRILLED to be introducing my friend Caroline to the web3/music nft space with our holiday collab exclusively on Sound! 

Brother Bird is the Nashville-based solo project of Caroline Swon. She embraces an intimate, ethereal style of indie rock in her 2018 self-titled EP, and has since worked closely with her friends/mentors Andy Hull & Robert McDowell of Manchester Orchestra on her first full length album, ‘gardens’. Released at the end of 2021, this record showcases a more energetic and playful sound from Swon, while still touching on her trademark vulnerability. 

In addition to joining Manchester Orchestra on the road for their co-headlining tour with The Front Bottoms, Swon has also opened up for several other artists such as Pete Yorn, Cavetown, Pinegrove, Bad Books, Lily & Madeleine, and Old Sea Brigade.
